# Interaction Patterns

## Hover Underline for Links

Footer and nav links use an `::after` pseudo-element underline:

```css
.link {
  position: relative;
}

.link::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  bottom: -2px;
  width: 0;
  height: 1px;
  background: currentColor;
  transition: width 0.3s ease;
}

.link:hover::after {
  width: 100%;
}
```

## FlairButton Hover

Never reimplement the flair hover effect. Always use the `FlairButton` component from `@/components/ui/FlairButton`.

- Default (`variant="light"`): white border + white fill on hover (for dark backgrounds)
- Dark (`variant="dark"`): black border + black fill on hover (for light backgrounds)
- Sizes: `sm` (header), `md` (default), `lg` (hero/CTA)

## Custom Cursor

Only use for specific interactive elements (e.g., video testimonials). Implementation:

- Track mouse position with `onMouseMove`
- Show/hide with `onMouseEnter` / `onMouseLeave`
- Position with `left` / `top` inline styles on an absolutely-positioned element
- Use `cursor: none` on the parent container

## Scroll Locking

Use `position: fixed` on `document.body` (not `overflow: hidden`) for cross-browser reliability:

```ts
function lockScroll() {
  const scrollY = window.scrollY;
  document.body.style.position = "fixed";
  document.body.style.top = `-${scrollY}px`;
  document.body.style.left = "0";
  document.body.style.right = "0";
  document.body.dataset.scrollLock = String(scrollY);
}

function unlockScroll() {
  const scrollY = document.body.dataset.scrollLock;
  document.body.style.position = "";
  document.body.style.top = "";
  // ... restore scroll position
}
```

## Carousel — Horizontal Scroll

Used by `BlogSection`:

```tsx
ref.current.scrollBy({ left: cardWidth + gap, behavior: "smooth" });
```

- Hide scrollbar: `scrollbar-width: none; -ms-overflow-style: none;` + `::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }`
- Use `ArrowNav` component for prev/next buttons

## Carousel — Vertical Slide

Used by `TestimonialsSection`:

- Track via `translateY(-${offset}px)` on the track element
- Wheel/touch events navigate between slides
- Use `CarouselDots` component for dot indicators
- Lock page scroll while user is interacting with the carousel

## Scroll Reveal Animation

Use the `ScrollReveal` component for fade-in-up entrance animations. Wraps any content with an intersection observer trigger.
